## Step 2: Write User Stories with ACORD Terminology

> **Update Todos** Identify insurance-specific functional r, Write user stories with ACORD terminolog, Define insurance business rules

Here are some initial user stories using ACORD terminology:

**US-001: Policy Quote Creation**
```
As an insurance agent
I want to create a quote for a prospective insured
So that I can provide a premium estimate before binding
Priority: High
Story Points: 8

Acceptance Criteria:
- AC-001.1: Agent selects policy type (AUTO, HOME, LIFE, HEALTH)
- AC-001.2: Agent enters insured details (name, DOB, address)
- AC-001.3: Agent selects coverages with limits and deductibles
- AC-001.4: System calculates premium using rating engine
- AC-001.5: System generates quote number (QUO-YYYY-NNNNNN)
- AC-001.6: Quote is valid for 30 days from creation

Error Scenarios:
- E-001.1: Coverage limit exceeds maximum → 400 with specific limit error
- E-001.2: Insured fails eligibility check → 422 with disqualification reason
- E-001.3: Rating engine cannot calculate → 500 with fallback to manual underwriting
```

**US-005: Claim Filing (FNOL)**
```
As a policyholder
I want to file a claim (First Notice of Loss)
So that I can initiate the claims process for a covered loss
Priority: High
Story Points: 8  

Acceptance Criteria:
- AC-005.1: System verifies policy is active on date of loss
- AC-005.2: System verifies claimed coverage type exists on policy
- AC-005.3: System assigns claim number (CLM-YYYY-NNNNNN)
- AC-005.4: System sets initial reserve based on estimated amount
- AC-005.5: System records loss description and date of loss
- AC-005.6: Claim status is set to FNOL

Error Scenarios:
- E-005.1: Policy not active on date of loss → 400 "Policy not active for date of loss"
- E-005.2: Coverage type not on policy → 400 "Coverage type not found on policy" 
- E-005.3: Estimated amount exceeds coverage limit → Warning (not error, but flagged)
```

